SIMPLE: uncurl
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uncurl
<hw>Un*curl"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>curl</ets>.]</ety> <def>To loose from curls, or
ringlets; to straighten out, as anything curled or curly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He sheaths his paw, <qex>uncurls</qex> his angry mane.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncurl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Uncurl
<hw>Un*curl"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become uncurled, or
straight.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uncurrent</ent>⟦br⟧
